<br>
points are intended to be awarded for serious RAIDS, ie: zone raids, quest raids, etc...not for simple exp groups, or such...in fact, the way that the exp groups/quest groups points system works is that whoever needs help with the quest has to pay, out of his/her own point pool, to recruit fellow members...i made a brief explanation of this with the example of the EK druid/ranger epic fight...well the same thing i think would go for the grey: if you need an amulet, and cant manage collecting organs solo, recruit 3-4 more people to help you (which would cost you 3-4 points, but would get you your amulet and some exp in return).  of course if there are multiple people that are going to get amulets, say, in a group of 6, then those people would "split the cost" of dealt out points...ie:3 of you all decide to group up to go get organs, but you would rather have a full group then just 3, for safety sake, so you recruit 3 scarab members at the cost of 1 point each - 3 points to pay out, divided by the 3 of you - to the recruited members, assuming that they dont want the amulet themselves and are there just to help you get yours...<br>
<br>
also i highly doubt we will have a zone that awards 40 points for raiding, ever...sure maybe sleepers tomb or ssra or POP zones will get close...but think for a moment: we cannot allow the points system to award more points to players then we can payback via loot...we cant give 100 players 20 points each for a naggy raid for example if we only get 40 total points worth of loot to begin with in the first place...<br>
<br>
this points system is going to be a rough start, and its not going to be fair, and its not going to be balanced nor is it going to be perfect - for awhile at least...so just bare with it, so we can all smooth it out to make it fair, balanced, and (as close as possible to) perfect....and if in the end we manage to get a memberbase that is mature enough and not so selfish/greedy/etc. (the common problems plaguing "pick-up" type raids and random grouping), then we can just scratch the entire points system alltogether...<br>
<br>
THE main point with the entire points system is to award effort, so that the player that always raids and always does his/her job well, that never causes problems, that is always obedient to raid leaders or even leads raids him/herself, wont get left out of the loot just because he/she has really bad luck with /random (or doesnt have a hacked eq DLL that replaces the random function!! although i think they mightve fixed that exploit since last i saw it hehe)<br>
